Snow. As RJ kindly pointed out MP3 format compresses the audio to make its
megabyte size smaller to take up less room in storage (hard drive or on a
network such as this yahoo group.)  WAV does not compress the audio and
therefore takes up a ton more room (or network space).  I have an ESNIPS
account like Misty pointed out where I post my WAV files for free.  



But my basic rule of thumb is to save the entire audio session as a .WAV
file.  Save my clips of messages on my computer in .WAV and .MP3.  I use the
MP3 format to post or upload into the files section on the groups.  I don&#39;t
keep the MP3 files once they have been posted online, listened to and
removed.  



Hopefully I haven&#39;t confused you.  Let me know..

k



